---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Scrabble Geometry Words — HEXAGON, POLYGON, VERTEX, PRISM, AXIS" description="High-scoring geometry words for Scrabble: HEXAGON (18pts), VERTEX (16pts), POLYGON (13pts), AXIS (11pts), PRISM (9pts). Math vocabulary advantage." keywords="scrabble geometry words, hexagon scrabble, vertex scrabble, polygon scrabble, axis scrabble, prism scrabble, math words scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Geometry Words — HEXAGON, POLYGON, VERTEX, PRISM, AXIS","description":"High-scoring geometry words: HEXAGON (18pts), VERTEX (16pts), POLYGON (13pts). Math vocabulary for Scrabble.","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-geometry-words"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What geometry words score highest in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"HEXAGON leads at 18 points (7 letters) with H(4)+X(8). VERTEX scores 16 points with V(4)+X(8). POLYGON scores 13 with P(3)+Y(4). These math terms use premium tiles naturally."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is HEXAGON valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, HEXAGON is valid in both SOWPODS and TWL. At 18 points and 7 letters, it's bingo-eligible earning the 50-point bonus. The H(4) and X(8) make it one of the highest-scoring common 7-letter words."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why are geometry words good for Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Geometry terms contain X (HEXAGON, VERTEX, AXIS), worth 8 points. They also use H, V, and Y frequently. These are everyday academic words that score like obscure Scrabble vocabulary."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Geometry Words — Math Vocabulary for Scrabble</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>4 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Geometry vocabulary is a Scrabble scoring powerhouse. The letter X appears in HEXAGON, VERTEX, and AXIS — three common math terms scoring 18, 16, and 11 points respectively. These aren't obscure words; they're terms everyone learned in school. POLYGON adds Y(4) for 13 points, and even PRISM scores 9 with its compact 5-letter frame. Math class finally paying off.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">18</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Top Score (HEXAGON)</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Words Featured</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">13.4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Avg Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">3/5</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Contain X</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top Geometry Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 TOP SCORER</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">HEXAGON</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">18 points · H(4)+E(1)+X(8)+A(1)+G(2)+O(1)+N(1) · Bingo eligible</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">H and X together deliver 12 points from just two tiles. At 7 letters, HEXAGON uses your entire rack for the 50-point bingo bonus.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 VERTEX</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">16 pts · 6 letters · V(4)+E(1)+R(1)+T(1)+E(1)+X(8)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10"><p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 POLYGON</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">13 pts · 7 letters · P(3)+O(1)+L(1)+Y(4)+G(2)+O(1)+N(1)</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ AXIS</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">11 pts · 4 letters · A(1)+X(8)+I(1)+S(1) · Short X word</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⭐ PRISM</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">9 pts · 5 letters · P(3)+R(1)+I(1)+S(1)+M(3) · P+M value</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Geometry Word Strategy</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X is the geometry letter:</span> Three of five words contain X (8pts). When you draw X, think shapes: HEXAGON (7, bingo), VERTEX (6, flexible), AXIS (4, tight spots). Geometry gives X multiple homes.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Short words for tight boards:</span> AXIS (4 letters, 11pts) and PRISM (5 letters, 9pts) play anywhere. When the board is locked, these compact math terms score well in parallel plays or tight corners.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">HEXAGON and POLYGON are bingos:</span> Both are 7 letters — use your entire rack for the 50-point bonus. HEXAGON scores 18+50=68 minimum. On a premium square, this can reach 100+ points.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">HEXAGON</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">VERTEX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">16pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">POLYGON</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">13pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">AXIS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">PRISM</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Geometry vocabulary is <span class="text-white font-medium">the best X-tile category</span> in Scrabble. Three common geometry words use X, giving you multiple options when you draw that 8-point tile. Memorise HEXAGON, VERTEX, and AXIS — your X always has a home.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-science-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Science Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words for Scrabble</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-nature-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Nature Words for Scrabble</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find geometry words from your tiles — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
